'''Murtaza Hassan''' (c. 1955 â€“ 11 April 2011), more commonly known by his stage name '''Mastana''', was a [[Pakistani people|Pakistani]] comedian, senior famous for his stage work. He worked in many stage shows like larri adda, yaro main luteya geya.
==Biography== Murtaza Hassan was born in [[Gujranwala]] and raised in [[Lahore]], before becoming a top comedian in famous Lahore theater. He has worked in more than 2,000 stage dramas in [[Lahore]] and in many different cities, Countries. He gained national popularity for his role of Uncle Keyon on the television series ''Shabdeg''. His co-stars, throughout his career, included such actors as [[Khalid Abbas Dar]], [[Babbu Baral]], [[Naseem Vicky]], [[Sohail Ahmed]], [[Tariq Teddy]], [[Iftikhar Thakur]], [[Amanat Chan]], [[Amanaullah|Amanullah]], [[Albella]] and [[Abid Khan]] [[Shoki Khan]] [[Qavi Khan]] [[Umer Shareef]] [[Moin Akhter]]. {{Citation needed|date=April 2011}} His famous role was " Uncle Q" and that was his serious role.
==Death== Murtaza Hassan died on 11 April 2011, at the Victoria Hospital in Bahawalpur. He was believed to be 57 years old. <!-- as per notice of death at www.thenews.com.pk/TodaysPrintDetail.aspx?ID=41224&Cat=2&dt=4/12/2011 --> He had been suffering from [[Hepatitis C]]. He was survived by his widow and a son, Hafiz M Saad Hassan.
